verbs.description: symbolize (third-person singular simple present symbolizes, present participle symbolizing, simple past and past participle symbolized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To be symbolic of; to represent.
(intransitive) To use symbols; to represent ideas symbolically.
(intransitive, obsolete) To resemble each other in qualities or properties; to correspond; to harmonize.
examples: They both symbolize in this, that they love to look upon themselves through multiplying glasses.

entries.meaning: (intransitive, obsolete) To hold the same faith; to agree.
